.name
Blitz
.author
Hayes Haugen 
.description
Blitz is a small program that is designed to be loaded into memory and that
sits in the background until activated by its hotkey.  It allows you to
view a text file, much like a TYPE command, only that it lets you move
forwards and backwards through the file.  Its screen updates are blitz'n.  
